TI  - DYNAMICS OF FOREST COVERAGE IN THE MUNICIPALITY OF CRISSIUMAL-RS DURING A PERIOD OF TWENTY YEARS
T2  - REVISTA ELETRONICA EM GESTAO EDUCACAO E TECNOLOGIA AMBIENTAL
AB  - The present study aims to assess the dynamics of forest cover in Crissiumal-RS, through remote sensing techniques. From the digital classification of satellite images from Landsat 5 TM sensor, between 1988 and 2008 were generated thematic maps use and land cover on the respective dates. These maps were later crossed through the Space for GIS Algebraic Language (LEGAL), which allowed determination of the following processes: maintaining forest, forest regeneration and deforestation. Among the main results is the increase in forest cover in 4756.33 ha and also the occurrence of 1508.04 ha of deforestation at the end of the period. The increase in forest cover may be combined with declining rural population and the abandonment of areas previously occupied by agriculture to comply with the law.
