TI  - Floristic and phytosociology of a lowland rain forest from Parque Estadual do Palmito, Paranagu, PR.
T2  - ARQUIVOS DE BIOLOGIA E TECNOLOGIA
AB  - The floristic and phytossociologic structure of the 100-year-old vegetation of the Parque Estadual do Palmito was studied in order to evaluate the regeneration after agricultural explotation in relation to different sucessional stages (12,15 and 50 years old). All trees with DAP greater than or equal to 5 cm in the 14 plots 200m(2) from hydromorphic Podzol soil were analysed. A total of 556 trees of 37 species (21 families, 32 genera) were studied. The physiognomy of the local vegetation is caracterized by 13 predominant species, representing nearly 80% of the sampled individuals. Among these, the most abun(1)dant are: palmiteiro (Euterpe edulis); cambui (Myrcia multiflora); mangue-brabo (C. criuva), and canela-pimenta (Ocotea pulchella).The species that charazterize of the 100-year forest are the same identified in the 12, 25 and 50 year old areas investigated. However, the importance value (VI) of each of these species varied among the sucessional stages.
