TI  - Recovery of lizard assembages 10 years after reduced-impact logging in central-eastern Amazonia
T2  - BIOTROPICA
AB  - Understanding changes in species composition due to human-induced habitat modification and environmental filtering is essential for formulating effective conservation strategies. Species turnover resulting from reduced-impact logging (RIL) is expected in the short term, generally with species adapted to open areas replacing those dependent on old-growth forest. However, little is known about how RIL activities influence assemblages after the perturbation ceased. We sampled lizards across an edaphic and vegetation-structure gradient in 64 plots in the Brazilian Amazon to test the hypothesis that changes in assemblage composition and proportion of heliothermic species are due to canopy openness resulting from ceased RIL activities and individual tree falls or to other environmental gradients. Contrary to expectations, canopy openness did not significantly affect the overall composition of lizard assemblages, but nearby unforested areas influenced assemblage composition, resulting in a higher proportion of heliothermic species. The composition of lizard assemblages was also significantly influenced by the distance to the nearest water body, vegetation height, and soil sand content. However, leaf litter height did not have a detectable impact on the composition of lizard assemblages. We conclude that short-term changes in species composition due to habitat modification by RIL do not persist in the long term after the perturbation ceases, and the assemblages may recover as vegetation regenerates. Although lizard species respond to spatial and temporal variation in environmental characteristics, we found evidence that lizard assemblages recover as reduced-impact logging (RIL) activities cease and vegetation regenerates.Abstract in Portuguese is available with online material.
   Compreender as mudan & ccedil;as na composi & ccedil;& atilde;o de esp & eacute;cies devido & agrave; modifica & ccedil;& atilde;o do habitat induzida pelo homem e & agrave; filtragem ambiental & eacute; essencial para a formula & ccedil;& atilde;o de estrat & eacute;gias eficazes de conserva & ccedil;& atilde;o. A substitui & ccedil;& atilde;o de esp & eacute;cies resultante da explora & ccedil;& atilde;o florestal de impacto reduzido (EIR) & eacute; esperada no curto prazo, geralmente com esp & eacute;cies adaptadas a & aacute;reas abertas substituindo aquelas dependentes de florestas prim & aacute;rias. No entanto, pouco se sabe sobre como as atividades de EIR influenciam as assembleias ap & oacute;s o t & eacute;rmino da perturba & ccedil;& atilde;o. Amostramos lagartos ao longo de um gradiente ed & aacute;fico e de estrutura de vegeta & ccedil;& atilde;o em 64 parcelas na Amaz & ocirc;nia brasileira para testar a hip & oacute;tese de que as mudan & ccedil;as na composi & ccedil;& atilde;o das assembleias e a propor & ccedil;& atilde;o de esp & eacute;cies heliot & eacute;rmicas s & atilde;o devidas & agrave; abertura do dossel resultante do t & eacute;rmino das atividades de EIR e de quedas individuais de & aacute;rvores, ou a outros gradientes ambientais. Contrariando as expectativas, a abertura do dossel n & atilde;o afetou significativamente a composi & ccedil;& atilde;o geral das assembleias de lagartos, mas & aacute;reas desflorestadas pr & oacute;ximas influenciaram a composi & ccedil;& atilde;o das assembleias, resultando em uma maior propor & ccedil;& atilde;o de esp & eacute;cies heliot & eacute;rmicas. A composi & ccedil;& atilde;o das assembleias de lagartos tamb & eacute;m foi significativamente influenciada pela dist & acirc;ncia at & eacute; o corpo d'& aacute;gua mais pr & oacute;ximo, altura da vegeta & ccedil;& atilde;o e teor de areia no solo. No entanto, a altura da serrapilheira n & atilde;o teve impacto detect & aacute;vel na composi & ccedil;& atilde;o das assembleias de lagartos. Conclu & iacute;mos que as mudan & ccedil;as de curto prazo na composi & ccedil;& atilde;o de esp & eacute;cies devido & agrave; modifica & ccedil;& atilde;o do habitat pela EIR n & atilde;o persistem no longo prazo ap & oacute;s o t & eacute;rmino da perturba & ccedil;& atilde;o, e as assembleias podem se recuperar & agrave; medida que a vegeta & ccedil;& atilde;o se regenera. Embora as assembleias de lagartos respondam & agrave; varia & ccedil;& atilde;o espacial e temporal das caracter & iacute;sticas ambientais, encontramos evid & ecirc;ncias de que essas assembleias se recuperam & agrave; medida que as atividades de EIR cessam e a vegeta & ccedil;& atilde;o se regenera.
